TITLE:: PanolaLilypond
summary:: render Panola voice(s) to a standalone LilyPond (.ly) document
categories:: Notation, Utils
related:: Classes/Panola, Classes/PanolaMEI, Classes/MSScore, Classes/PanolaMeterSplitter

DESCRIPTION::
Pure transform from Panola voice(s) + score preferences to a self-contained LilyPond source (a String)
that renders standalone (teletype::lilypond score.ly::) and is also accepted by MusicScene's LilyPond
engraver. It is the LilyPond sibling of link::Classes/PanolaMEI:: and covers the same features: meter-aware
splitting-and-tying, tuplets (incl. music21-style completion and cross-barline splitting), dynamics,
articulations, slurs, hairpins, lyrics, inline teletype::@clef::, mid-piece meter/key changes, additive
meters, page/system breaks, braces and multi-staff. Pitches are absolute with teletype::\\language "english"::;
LilyPond auto-beams and auto-respells accidentals. See link::Classes/PanolaMEI:: for the Panola property syntax.



CLASSMETHODS::

METHOD:: pr_pitchLy
(private) a Panola pitch (pname, accid code s/x/f/ff or nil, octave Integer) as an absolute english-language LilyPond pitch, e.g. teletype::fs''::. Octave marks: apostrophes = octave-3 (comma below).

ARGUMENT:: pname
the diatonic pitch letter String (a..g)

ARGUMENT:: accid
the accidental code String "s"/"x"/"f"/"ff", or nil

ARGUMENT:: oct
the octave Integer (scientific: 4 = the octave of middle C)

returns:: a LilyPond pitch String
METHOD:: pr_durLy
(private) a MEI/Panola duration value token ("1","2","4","8",... or "breve"/"long"/"maxima") plus a dot count as a LilyPond duration, e.g. teletype::4.::

ARGUMENT:: md
the note-value token (a String or Integer)

ARGUMENT:: dots
the number of augmentation dots

returns:: a LilyPond duration String
METHOD:: pr_clefLy
(private) a clef Symbol (\treble \bass \alto \tenor) as a LilyPond clef name; an unknown clef warns and yields "treble".

ARGUMENT:: clefSym
a clef Symbol

returns:: a LilyPond clef-name String
METHOD:: pr_keyLy
(private) a key Symbol (e.g. \Gmajor, \FsharpMinor) as a LilyPond teletype::\key:: argument, e.g. teletype::g \major::; an unknown key warns and yields teletype::c \major::. LilyPond auto-respells accidentals, so no per-note key logic is needed.

ARGUMENT:: keySym
a key Symbol

returns:: a LilyPond key String, e.g. "g \\major"
METHOD:: pr_meterLy
(private) a meter String as a LilyPond time-signature command. A plain numerator (teletype::"7/8"::) yields teletype::\time 7/8::; an additive numerator (teletype::"2+2+3/8"::) yields a teletype::\compoundMeter:: that both displays the additive signature and groups the auto-beaming.

ARGUMENT:: meterStr
a meter String, e.g. "4/4" or "2+2+3/8"

returns:: a LilyPond time-signature command String
METHOD:: pr_dynLy
(private) a dynamic mark String as a LilyPond dynamic: predefined marks (teletype::mf::, teletype::sfz::, ...) become teletype::\mf::; a non-standard mark falls back to a teletype::\markup \dynamic:: text.

ARGUMENT:: mark
a dynamic mark String (e.g. "mf", "sffz")

returns:: a LilyPond post-event String
METHOD:: pr_artLy
(private) a space-separated MEI articulation-code list as concatenated LilyPond scripts (teletype::acc stacc:: -> teletype::->-.::). LilyPond has no spiccato script, so teletype::spicc:: maps to the staccatissimo wedge.

ARGUMENT:: articStr
a space-separated MEI artic-code String (e.g. "acc stacc"), or ""

returns:: a concatenated LilyPond script String, or ""
METHOD:: pr_lyricTok
(private) one lyric syllable slot as a LilyPond lyricmode token: the (quoted if it contains a space/hyphen/underscore/quote or leads with a digit) syllable, plus teletype:: --:: when it continues to the next syllable of the same word. A melisma/blank note is emitted as teletype::_:: by the caller, not here.

ARGUMENT:: slot
a syllable slot Event (syl:, con:)

returns:: a LilyPond lyricmode token String


